ABERRANT: Evil bound by a personal code of honor

Aberrant characters are evil, but evil with structure.  They have a
personal code of honor, not a moral one but a practical one, and they
follow it absolutely.  They may be killers, predators, and manipulators,
but they keep their word, respect strength, and have rules they will not
break.

An Aberrant character might be a mercenary who always delivers what they
are paid for, a gang lord who protects their own turf viciously but will
not harm children, or a monster who hunts only those it considers worthy
prey.  Their evil is cold, disciplined, and ultimately more frightening
for it.

GUIDELINES
  - Evil but bound by a self-imposed code (which may seem bizarre to
    others)
  - Will keep their word: it is a point of pride even when costly
  - Uses lies and manipulation as tools, but selectively
  - Will harm and kill without remorse when it serves their code
  - Has a rigid sense of what is acceptable within their own framework
  - Despises cowardice, treachery against one's own, and breaking of
    oaths

Aberrant characters are the disciplined predators of the Rifts world:
the Splugorth slaver who honors the terms of a deal once struck, the
Gargoyle warlord who demands tribute but does not raid those who pay,
the assassin whose reputation for reliability is their most valuable
asset.

They are more predictable than Miscreants and can be dealt with: at a
cost.  Good characters find them deeply unsettling: more dangerous than
chaotic evil precisely because they are controlled.

